        "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,192 @@\n+# Task Packet\n+\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-110\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+TIMESTAMP: 2026-05-23_10-25-49+0300\n+RELATED_FILES:\n+- tools/architecture-lints/src/kernel_isolation.rs\n+- tools/architecture-lints/tests/kernel_isolation_test.rs\n+- Cargo.toml\n+- crates/io-gltf/Cargo.toml\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/animation.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/asset_store_cache.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/cache_stub.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/export.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/handles.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/image.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/import.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/lib.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/material.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/mesh.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/scene_builder.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/scene_stub.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/src/skeleton.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/animated_character_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/cube_round_trip.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/pbr_material_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/smooth_normal_sphere_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/textured_cube_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/textured_uv_cube_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/uv_cube_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/tests/common/mod.rs\n+- crates/io-image/Cargo.toml\n+- crates/io-image/src/error.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/exr.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/format_detect.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/hdr.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/image_data.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/jpeg.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/lib.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/mip_chain.rs\n+- crates/io-image/src/png.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/mip_chain_test.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/round_trip_exr.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/round_trip_hdr.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/round_trip_jpeg.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/round_trip_png.rs\n+- crates/io-image/tests/common/mod.rs\n+- crates/io-step/Cargo.toml\n+- crates/io-step/src/lib.rs\n+- crates/io-stl/Cargo.toml\n+- crates/io-stl/src/lib.rs\n+STATUS: OPEN\n+\n+## Goal\n+\n+Perform a read-only preflight audit for GitHub issue #110, \"Audit io-format metadata declarations.\" The purpose is to determine the exact `[package.metadata.rge].formats` declarations that should later be added for the target IO crates, without changing any source, tests, docs, manifests, lockfiles, workflows, scripts, lints, or existing handoff packets in this dispatch.\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+### MAY edit\n+- None. This is an audit-only preflight.\n+\n+### MUST NOT edit\n+- Cargo.toml\n+- Cargo.lock\n+- tools/architecture-lints/src/kernel_isolation.rs\n+- tools/architecture-lints/tests/kernel_isolation_test.rs\n+- crates/io-gltf/**\n+- crates/io-image/**\n+- crates/io-step/**\n+- crates/io-stl/**\n+- .github/workflows/**\n+- .ai/**\n+- tools/**\n+- scripts/**\n+- docs/**\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-110_TASK_2026-05-23_10-25-49+0300.md\n+- Any existing handoff packet\n+- Any source, test, documentation, schema, lint, workflow, script, or generated lockfile\n+\n+### MAY add new files\n+- Exactly one new `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-110_EXEC_*.md` execution report packet for this dispatch.\n+- The matching `.meta.json` sidecar may be produced by `new-handoff.ps1 -Finalize` if the orchestrator or executor finalizes the EXEC packet.\n+\n+### MUST NOT add new files\n+- Any new source, test, documentation, schema, lint, workflow, script, fixture, manifest, lockfile, or local audit artifact.\n+- Any new packet other than the single ISSUE-110 EXEC report.\n+\n+## Deliverables\n+\n+- A read-only `EXECUTION_REPORT` that states no source/manifests/tests/docs/lints/scripts/workflows were edited.\n+- A section titled exactly `## IO Formats Metadata Preflight Answers` containing exactly these five numbered questions and answers:\n+  1. `What metadata shape does the lint read?`\n+  2. `Which workspace IO crates are detected?`\n+  3. `What exact four-crate format arrays are implied?`\n+  4. `Which ownership ambiguities and aliases are resolved, and which remain?`\n+  5. `What is the smallest safe follow-up?`\n+- The exact four-crate format arrays must be identified as:\n+  - `rge-io-gltf`: `[\"gltf\", \"glb\"]`\n+  - `rge-io-image`: `[\"png\", \"jpg\", \"jpeg\", \"exr\", \"hdr\"]`\n+  - `rge-io-step`: `[\"step\", \"stp\", \"iges\", \"igs\"]`\n+  - `rge-io-stl`: `[\"stl\"]`\n+- The answer block must explicitly resolve these aliases and ownership points:\n+  - `jpg` and `jpeg` both belong to `rge-io-image`.\n+  - `step` and `stp` both belong to `rge-io-step`.\n+  - `iges` and `igs` both belong to `rge-io-step`.\n+  - `gltf` and `glb` both belong to `rge-io-gltf`.\n+  - Embedded raster bytes inside glTF/GLB remain codec-owned by `rge-io-image`; `rge-io-gltf` owns glTF/GLB container and embedding semantics only.\n+- The report must identify the current lint metadata shape from `tools/architecture-lints/src/kernel_isolation.rs`: each IO crate opts in with `[package.metadata.rge]` and `formats = [...]`, strings are lower-case extension names with no leading dot, and missing metadata is currently a stderr warning rather than a violation.\n+- The report must list IO workspace members detected from root `Cargo.toml` and lint detection rules, including at minimum `crates/io-gltf`, `crates/io-step`, `crates/io-stl`, `crates/io-obj`, `crates/io-image`, `crates/io-audio`, and `crates/io-3mf`; only the four target crates above require exact arrays in this dispatch.\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- The EXEC report confirms read-only inspection of all required files and directories:\n+  - `tools/architecture-lints/src/kernel_isolation.rs`\n+  - `tools/architecture-lints/tests/kernel_isolation_test.rs`\n+  - root `Cargo.toml`\n+  - `crates/io-gltf/**`\n+  - `crates/io-image/**`\n+  - `crates/io-step/**`\n+  - `crates/io-stl/**`\n+- The EXEC report contains the exact `## IO Formats Metadata Preflight Answers` section with all five required questions answered.\n+- The EXEC report identifies the exact four arrays listed in `Deliverables`, or halts with `STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, `HANDOFF_STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, and `NEXT_ROLE: HUMAN_ARBITER`.\n+- The EXEC report explicitly resolves or halts on `jpg`/`jpeg`, `step`/`stp`, `iges`/`igs`, and glTF/GLB embedded raster ownership.\n+- The smallest follow-up must be a separate, later metadata-only manifest edit dispatch that adds `[package.metadata.rge] formats = [...]` to the four target crate `Cargo.toml` files, with no implementation or lint behavior changes bundled into that follow-up.\n+- `git diff -- Cargo.toml Cargo.lock tools/architecture-lints crates/io-gltf crates/io-image crates/io-step crates/io-stl .github .ai` shows no source, manifest, lockfile, lint, workflow, script, test, or doc modifications from this dispatch.\n+\n+## Constraints / Non-Goals\n+\n+- Do not edit any `Cargo.toml` in this dispatch. If the audit proves a manifest edit is needed, report it as the smallest follow-up and stop.\n+- Do not run local cargo commands of any kind.\n+- Do not run tests, formatters, architecture lints, `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1`, or other verification scripts.\n+- Do not modify lint behavior, lint tests, source code, crate metadata, docs, workflows, scripts, schemas, `Cargo.lock`, or existing packets.\n+- Do not add alias normalization logic to the architecture lint.\n+- Do not decide exact format arrays for non-target IO crates such as `io-obj`, `io-audio`, or `io-3mf`; list them as detected workspace IO members only unless inspected evidence from the required files makes a limited ownership note unavoidable.\n+- Do not infer dispatch completion from missing `_REVIEW_` or `_CLOSEOUT_` packets.\n+\n+## Verification Gates\n+\n+The Executor MUST run and document the result of each of these in their `EXECUTION_REPORT`:\n+\n+- Read-only inspection using shell file reads and search commands only, covering every required path listed in `Acceptance Criteria`; expected result: evidence sufficient to answer all five preflight questions.\n+- `git status --short --untracked-files=all` before writing the EXEC report and again after writing it; expected result: no executor-attributed source, manifest, lockfile, lint, workflow, script, test, doc, or `.ai` changes. The already-completed ISSUE-110 TASK packet is a planner artifact, and the new ISSUE-110 EXEC packet plus optional EXEC sidecar are allowed protocol artifacts.\n+- `git diff -- Cargo.toml Cargo.lock tools/architecture-lints crates/io-gltf crates/io-image crates/io-step crates/io-stl .github .ai`; expected result: no output.\n+- `new-handoff.ps1 -Finalize -PacketPath ai_handoffs/ISSUE-110_EXEC_*.md -DryRun` using the actual execution report path; expected result: exit 0.\n+\n+## Halt Conditions\n+\n+The Executor MUST halt and write an EXEC report with `STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, `HANDOFF_STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, `NEXT_ROLE: HUMAN_ARBITER`, and `EXIT_CODE: 0` if any of the following occur:\n+\n+- Any required file or directory cannot be inspected.\n+- The executor cannot identify exact arrays for `rge-io-gltf`, `rge-io-image`, `rge-io-step`, and `rge-io-stl` from the inspected files.\n+- Any alias or ownership point cannot be resolved for `jpg`/`jpeg`, `step`/`stp`, `iges`/`igs`, or glTF/GLB embedded raster bytes.\n+- Any answer would require editing a `Cargo.toml`, lint source, lint test, source file, doc, workflow, script, `Cargo.lock`, or existing packet.\n+- Any local cargo command, test, formatter, architecture lint, or `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` would be needed to answer the five questions.\n+- The working tree shows source, manifest, lockfile, lint, workflow, script, test, doc, or `.ai` modifications attributable to this dispatch.\n+\n+## Planner Notes\n+\n+The lint currently reads package metadata through cargo metadata, extracts `package.metadata.rge.formats`, lowercases string entries, and reports duplicate claimed formats across detected IO crates. Missing metadata is deliberately only a warning. This dispatch is the preflight that should make the later manifest-only metadata edit obvious and small, not the edit itself.\n+\n+Planner\u0027s expected preflight outcome is that the four target arrays are exactly:\n+\n+```toml\n+# crates/io-gltf/Cargo.toml\n+[package.metadata.rge]\n+formats = [\"gltf\", \"glb\"]\n+\n+# crates/io-image/Cargo.toml\n+[package.metadata.rge]\n+formats = [\"png\", \"jpg\", \"jpeg\", \"exr\", \"hdr\"]\n+\n+# crates/io-step/Cargo.toml\n+[package.metadata.rge]\n+formats = [\"step\", \"stp\", \"iges\", \"igs\"]\n+\n+# crates/io-stl/Cargo.toml\n+[package.metadata.rge]\n+formats = [\"stl\"]\n+```\n+\n+This packet intentionally requires a halt rather than a manifest edit if any part of that answer cannot be supported by the inspected files.\n+\n+---\n+\n+HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-110\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+NEXT_ROLE: EXECUTOR_AI\n+EXIT_CODE: 0\n+\n+---"
